 ago) was concerning the "Pokemon Train" where people were wondering why Mr. Naka had pictures of Pokemon on the ST website. It turns out that this entry of the diary was comparing Pokemon's train advertisements to the Sonic Adventure train advertisements before its launch. And he mentioned how the SA advertisement campaign was much smaller than how Pokemon is being advertised.   <p><center><table border=0> <tr><td> <p><img src=http://www.sonicteam.com/fromteam/train/train04.jpg> </td><td> <img src=http://www.sonicteam.com/fromteam/train/soni1.gif>   </td></tr> </table></center> <p>I'll be going through my translator pretty much half the day. So if I find anything interesting, I'll be sure to post it here! Later! ^___^  <p><b>Source:</b> <a href=http://www.sonicteam.com target="_whole"> Sonic Team</a><br>
